  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>antro-pyloro-duodenal pressure</measure>
    <time_frame>3h</time_frame>
    <description>the main outcome is the pressure measured using pressure sensors within the antrum, the pylorus, and the first part of the duodenum. This will be measured during 3h fast. Pressures measured in the antrum, the pylorus, and the duodenum wiil be compared between healthy volunteers and gastroparetic patients</description>
  </primary_outcome>
